==English==
===Etymology===
[[Coin]]ed by television writer Jonathan Collier for ''The Simpsons'' episode 3F13, "Lisa the Iconoclast".

===Adjective===
'''cromulent'''

#''(Nonce word):'' Authentic; often used [[ironic]]ally, to claim [[authentic]]ity for [[something]] known to be [[otherwise]].  Often with an [[ironic]] "[[perfect]]ly".
#:'''Quotations'''
#:*He's [[embiggen]]ed that role with his '''cromulent''' performance. — Principal Skinner in ''The Simpsons''
#:*It's a perfectly '''cromulent''' word. — Ms. Hoover in ''The Simpsons''

# Something that is upper-class or sophisticated; a comment that is perfect for the occasion, insightful, often reffering to the word itself.

